Package org.modelio.api.module.lifecycle

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IModuleLifeCycleHandler
    The life cycle handler of a module is a set of methods that are called by Modelio on some events related to the module lifecycle in the project (such as starting, selecting, stopping and so on...)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DefaultModuleLifeCycleHandler
    Default implementation of the IModuleLifeCycleHandler interface.
